Description: Small stylized anthropomorphic figure used as an amulet, carved of bone, in a standing posture. The body and curved legs do not show any details, only the face is carved more in detail. A horizontal perforation drilled through the head enables a use as amulet, three small holes as decoration at its frontal part and three at the back.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), in redim, below level I, wall E13.2, East of room Y
Acquisition notes: 1949 Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
